<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
Total body length ranged from 16-17 mm. Tail 3.71% of body length. Hooks 7. Anterior teeth 27-28 and posterior teeth 30-35, respectively. Opaque and rigid body (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="F21" captionText="Figure 21. A Zonosagitta bedoti (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704205" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">21</figureCitation>
). Head wider than body (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Intestinal diverticular (shown by white arrow) A Aidanosagitta regularis (present) B Ferosagitta robusta (present) C Zonosagitta nagae (absent) D Zonosagitta bedoti (absent)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704191" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">7D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="F21" captionText="Figure 21. A Zonosagitta bedoti (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704205" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">21A</figureCitation>
). Short and dense teeth. Intestinal diverticula absent (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Intestinal diverticular (shown by white arrow) A Aidanosagitta regularis (present) B Ferosagitta robusta (present) C Zonosagitta nagae (absent) D Zonosagitta bedoti (absent)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704191" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">7D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="F21" captionText="Figure 21. A Zonosagitta bedoti (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704205" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">21B</figureCitation>
). 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“D”">&quot;D&quot;</normalizedToken>
-shaped eyes with star-shaped eye pigments (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="F21" captionText="Figure 21. A Zonosagitta bedoti (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704205" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">21B</figureCitation>
). Corona ciliata beginning behind eyes and elongated over neck (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="F21" captionText="Figure 21. A Zonosagitta bedoti (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704205" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">21B</figureCitation>
). Anterior fins 26.5% of body length. Anterior fins beginning at middle of ventral ganglion, anterior of anterior fins narrow with rayless zone and posterior of anterior fins partially rayed. Anterior fins 1.3 times longer than posterior fins. Starting points of anterior fins 34.3% and ending points of anterior fins 60.0% of body length, respectively (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="F21" captionText="Figure 21. A Zonosagitta bedoti (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704205" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">21A, D</figureCitation>
). Posterior fins 19.8% of body length. Starting points of posterior fins 63.7% and ending points of posterior fins 89.7% of body length, respectively. Posterior fins connected with anterior fins (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="F21" captionText="Figure 21. A Zonosagitta bedoti (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704205" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">21A</figureCitation>
). Caudal fin triangular-shaped and completely rayed (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="F21" captionText="Figure 21. A Zonosagitta bedoti (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704205" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">21C</figureCitation>
). Seminal vesicles spherical in shape with lateral rupture in mature specimen (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="F21" captionText="Figure 21. A Zonosagitta bedoti (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704205" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">21C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
